node.title: Sydney's Warragamba Dam overflows, fresh flood warnings issued
node.alt: A man wades through flood waters outside a house
node.description: NSW emergency services are urging people to remain alert to changing conditions with new flood warnings for several communities, while in Queensland, people have been rescued from flash flooding overnight.
node.content:
["Sydney's Warragamba Dam is overflowing\u00a0after reaching\u00a0capacity overnight, with fresh flood warnings\u00a0issued for communities downstream, as well as in the New South Wales Upper Hunter.", "WaterNSW spokesperson Tony Webber said Sydney's main water catchment reached capacity about 9pm Friday and the overflow is spilling into the\u00a0Hawkesbury-Nepean River.\u00a0", "\"Projections hold steady around at an estimated peak rate of 60-80\u00a0gigalitres per day,\" he said.", "\"We\u00a0expect some impacts in the river downstream.\"", "As the rain eases, all eyes are turning to flooded rivers.", "
Residents inspect damage
", "Residents in NSW's Upper Hunter have started to assess the damage to their homes now that\u00a0floodwaters are\u00a0receding.", "At least six homes in Scone were inundated on Friday\u00a0afternoon, with some reporting\u00a020 centimetres of water indoors.", "The NSW\u00a0SES is warning people to remain alert to changing conditions, with fresh\u00a0flood warnings now issued for several\u00a0communities.", "The flood peak is now approaching the town of Denman downstream.", "Preparations are also underway in Singleton, where moderate to major flooding is expected later today.", "The Bureau of Meteorology (BOM) has issued flood warnings for the Lachlan River and the Namoi, near Gunnedah and Narrabri.", "NSW SES spokesperson,\u00a0Adam Jones has asked people to remain vigilant after 17 flood rescues on Friday.", "\"We're really appreciative of the community who are adhering to the message of not riding, driving or walking through floodwater,\" he said.", "\"Those 17 yesterday were too many but as a whole \u2026 we're really seeing a [positive] trend and we want to thank those [people].\"", "
Flash flooding hits South-East\u00a0Queensland
", "Emergency services responded to two rescues in south-east Queensland overnight, with heavy rainfall causing flash flooding.\u00a0", "A swift water rescue crew launched a boat at Tingoora, in the South Burnett, where two cars became stuck in floodwaters.\u00a0", "Two people were rescued from each vehicle, and a dog was also retrieved. \u00a0", "In the Scenic Rim, Queensland Fire and Emergency Services brought in an excavator just before midnight to help get to two campers stuck in rising waters at Barney View."]
